Definition: a kind of thermometer consisting of two wires of different metals that are joined at both ends
Example: one junction is at the temperature to be measured and the other is held at a fixed lower temperature; the current generated in the circuit is proportional to the temperature difference
Synonyms: thermocouple_junction, thermometer, a, kind, of, consisting, two, wires, different, metals, that, are, joined, at, both, ends, one, junction, is, the, temperature, to, be, measured, and, other, held, fixed, lower, current, generated, in, circuit, proportional, difference
Category: noun.artifact
